  "title": "Degree of Freedom and Specific Heat",
  "concepts": [
    {
      "title": "Degree of Freedom for Monoatomic Gases",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Degree of Freedom for Monoatomic Gases</strong></h3><p>$\\text{f}=$ total degree of freedom</p><p>$\\text{f}=3$ translational</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ f}=3$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"219\" height=\"178\"></p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db58c03b9dcaf1afe153"
    },
    {
      "title": "Degree of Freedom for Diatomic Gases",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Degree of Freedom for Diatomic Gases</strong></h3><p>$f=3$ trans +2 rotational</p><p>(rotation along the bond axis) is neglected</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{f}=5\\to $ at ordinary temp.</p><p><strong>But at high temp., </strong>$\\text{f}=7$</p><p><strong>Reason : </strong>2 degree of freedom are also contributed by vibrational motion.</p><p>For high temperature, vibrational motion cannot be neglected, hence</p><p>it must also be counted.</p><p>At high temp.</p><p>$\\text{f}=3$ trans. +2 rotat. +2 vibrat. $=7$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"236\" height=\"199\"></p>",
      "position": 1,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db58c03b9dcaf1afe154"
    },
    {
      "title": "Degree of Freedom for Polyatomic Gases",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Degree of Freedom for Polyatomic Gases</strong></h3><p>$\\text{f}=3$ trans +3 rotations $=6$</p><p>$\\text{f}=6$ At low temp.</p><p>At high temp. $\\text{f}=3$ trans +3 rotat +2 vib.</p><p>$\\text{f}=8$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"221\" height=\"199\">&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>",
      "position": 2,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db58c03b9dcaf1afe155"
    }
  ],
